            "type": "text",
            "text": "Emergency Support and Load Bank Testing Requirements"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Emergency support is a vital component of power management for Brisbane's industrial and commercial sectors where power loss equates to significant financial risk. Load bank testing is the only definitive way to verify that a diesel generator can handle its rated capacity without risking 'wet stacking' or engine damage during a real emergency. This process involves applying an artificial load to the engine to test its performance under stress."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ul",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Schedule annual load bank testing to clear carbon deposits from the engine and exhaust system."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "li",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "lic",
                "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Establish a 24/7 emergency response protocol with a local Brisbane technician to minimise downtime."
